+# Recursive Exact Closure Must Use The Full Active Ledger And Exact Projected Helical Coefficients
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` recursive-closure requirement with `INFERRED` operational
+freeze
+
+Exact-support searches should close recursively from the conjugate-completed
+seed ledger. Each pass tests every ordered pair of active modes against exact
+triad relations using the exact Leray-projected helical interaction
+coefficient, adds every nonzero forced target mode with its conjugate
+completion, and then repeats with the enlarged active set until a fixed point
+or declared budget spill.
+
+A first-generation-only pass is not an honest exact closure audit. Repeated or
+otherwise degenerate triads are not exemptions: if the frozen projected
+coefficient is nonzero, the resulting mode belongs on the closure ledger.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/library-inbox/step-001-exploration-002-exact-search-class-closure-and-escalation-freeze.md`
